 =Otahuhu Borough Council\n| page = 3\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume LIX, Issue 122\n| date = 1928-05-25\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19280525.2.27\n| accessdate = 2019-10-02}}</ref>  Prior to the Round 11 matches W. Mapi, the halfback of the Mangere team died after a short illness. The team wore white armbands for their match with [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] in honour of him.\n\nGrafton Athletic won the competition after an undefeated season.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | 1928 B Grade Results\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 28 April <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Senior B Matches\n| page =13 \n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LXV, Issue 19933\n| date = 1928-03-30\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19280430.2.152.10\n| accessdate = 2019-09-30}}</ref>\n|| Parnell || 13 || Mangere || 5 || Carlaw Park # 2, 3:15pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 28 April || Northcote || 10 || Point Chevalier || 9 || Stafford Park, Northcote, 3pm<ref>{{cite news \n| title =New Playing Ground/The Area at Northcote/Opened by Mayor\n| page = 10\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LXV, Issue 19933\n| date = 1928-03-30\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19280430.2.101\n| accessdate = 2019-09-30}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 28 April || Otahuhu || 13 || Grafton || 15 || Otahuhu Reserve, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 2\n| 5 May <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Senior B Grade\n| page = 13\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LXV, Issue 19939\n| date = 1928-05-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19280507.2.151\n| accessdate = 2019-09-30}}</ref>|| Grafton || 12 || Parnell || 12 || Auckland Domain # 1, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 5 May || Mangere || 8 || Kingsland || 6 || Auckland Domain # 3, 3pm\n|-\n! sco